wikipedia_page.main: Ernest Noel, FGS (18 August 1831 – 20 May 1931) was Member of Parliament (MP)  for the Scottish seat of Dumfries Burghs from  1874 to 1886. He was chairman of the Artizans, Labourers & General Dwellings Company from 1880, during the construction of a new suburb for the working classes in Wood Green which was named "Noel Park" in his honour.
